History[edit]
Merger and expansion[edit]
Curtiss-Wright came into existence on July 5, 1929, the result of a merger of 12 companies associated with Curtiss Aeroplane and Motor Company of Buffalo, New York, and Wright Aeronautical of Dayton, Ohio,[2] and was headquartered in Buffalo, New York. With $75 million in capital (equivalent to 10.46 billion in 2016), it was the largest aviation company in the country.


Companies Merged[3]
Owner


Wright Aeronautical Corp
Hoyt


Curtiss Aeroplane & Motor Co
